article.headline: UTEP 72, Occidental 46
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Omar Thomas and Giovanni St. Amant scored 17 points apiece as Texas-El Paso beat Division III Occidental 72-46 on Tuesday night. Thomas was 7-of-14 from the field, and St. Amant was 6-of-10. The Miners (8-2) never trailed. Sam Betty led Occidental with 13 points. Ivan Kostic scored 11. Occidental (6-2) shot less than 40 percent from the game, including a paltry 33.3 percent in the second half. The Tigers trailed 38-22 at halftime.
